    <item>
      <title>Power Automate: Filter Emails Which Have No Category</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025/05/how-to-filter-email-category/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 24 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025/05/how-to-filter-email-category/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;in-this-article-i-want-to-show-you-how-to-filter-no-category-email-in-outlook-via-power-automate&#34;&gt;In this Article I want to show you how to filter no category email in outlook via Power Automate.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In current Outlook 365 connector, there is no option to filter out emails with/without categories.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When I tried to build the flow, I thought I could use &lt;code&gt;Get emails (V3)&lt;/code&gt;. After I tried I realised that there is no info in the body, but it doesn&amp;rsquo;t have the categories information, and the &lt;code&gt;most important thing is it may consume more API if I use it first&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
